This project contains an Apple Reminders library for Python, called `apple_reminders`.

We also provide a command-line tool called `rem` for managing Apple Reminders, which uses this library. It acts as an example of library usage.

All of our development environment is managed through `devenv`, while our virtual environments are setup with `uv` and automatically loaded by `devenv`. So it is important to run all of your commands from within `devenv shell`.

You can check for typing errors with `devenv shell mypy .`. Avoid using `type: ignore` and instead fix the typing errors as much as possible.

Our tests are written with `pytest`, so you can run them with `devenv shell pytest -v .`.
